LIMPOPO police have arrested 12 people. They face charges of possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition, and poaching. The suspects were arrested in three separate incidents throughout the province. Police spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe they were nabbed in the Hoedspruit, Zebediela and Mokopane policing areas on Tuesday. “Four men between the ages of 23 and 44 were arrested for poaching at a farm in Hoedspruit,” said Ngoepe. He said the police were acting on a tip-off. “Investigations led to the arrest of another suspect driving a getaway car.” The police stopped him, but he did not co-operate. The suspect was shot and injured. He was taken to hospital for medical treatment. Ngoepe said the driver of a second getaway car abandoned the vehicle and fled on foot. “He is still at large. Other suspects, aged between 23 and 35, were bust for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition in Zebediela. “Two more men were arrested in Mokopane for the same offence,” he said. The suspects will appear in the Mokopane, Lebowakgomo and Hoedspruit magistrates courts soon.